 DATA FILES AND THEIR SECURITY
-------------------------------
 You will be storing your information on your backup copy of the DAY-BY-DAY
program disk. It will contain all the information that you will be typing
into the system in future. It is therefore very important to keep a backup
copy of the disk on a regular basis, in case a fault develops.

 Although time consuming, imagine how much time it will take you to re-type
say, 100 appointments. Faults can develop on discs and it can be very
difficult or impossible to recover your lost data.



 CAPACITY
----------
 DAY-BY-DAY can store up to 1,000 messages in memory. This may be limited
by the amount of available memory, or by storing a number of unusually large
messages. You will be able to store more messages by removing any memory
resident programs or utilities.



 DATES
-------
 When entering a date the following prompt will appear on the screen:

             Day   :    DD
             Month :    MM
             Year  :    YY

 DD, MM and YY are the default values for the date, Simply press RETURN once
to accept the default date. Alternatively, enter the date required, DAY-BY-
DAY uses two digit years.

 Additionally, in the day prompt, three letter abbreviations for the day of
the week may be entered (e.g. Tue). The date will then be automatically
calculated within a week of the current day. In the Month Prompt, three
letter abbreviations may also be entered (e.g. Jan).

 DAY-BY-DAY will check for invalid dates.

 Intelligence !
 DAY-BY-DAY is intelligent in that it automatically changes the default as
you are entering the date. If you enter a new day which is less than the
current day displayed. DAY-BY-DAY will assume that you are starting a new
month. Similarly, if you enter a month which is less than the current
month displayed, it will assume that you are starting a new year.

 For example, assuming the default date is 31.12.88, if you enter 1 for the
day, DAY-BY-DAY will automatically change the default date to 1.1.89.



 SAVING AND LOADING INFORMATION
--------------------------------
 DAY-BY-DAY uses only one data file (called DBDDATA) which is stored on the
same disk as the program. This is automatically loaded when you load DAY-BY
-DAY and you will be prompted to save the file when exiting the program (if
you have made any changes).

 Hard-disk users please note : This data file will be loaded/saved to the
current directory (i.e. the directory from which you loaded DAY-BY-DAY).



 MODES OF OPERATION
--------------------
 DAY-BY-DAY is divided into two modes of operation - SCREEN and MENU.

SCREEN - This mode is for displaying/adding/editing your messages.
         Additionally, it is used for weekly/monthly summaries.

MENU - This mode is for selecting options for setting up categories
       searching for messages, selecting to display weekly/monthly planners.



