 MESSAGES
----------
 A category heading appears at the top of each screen. Messages are
displayed in the following format (this depends on whether you have
specified a date, time or duration).

  DATE    TIME    DURATION
  MESSAGE

 For example,

  Sun 1 Jan 1988 10.00-11.30 Morning
  Metting with Jerry.



 SCREEN OPTIONS
----------------
 The following are displayed at the bottom of the screen:

 (P)rev (N)ext (A)dd (D)elete (U)pdate (B)ackward (F)orward (O)utput (E)xit


 SELECTING A SCREEN OPTION
---------------------------
 Simply type the first letter corresponding to the screen option (e.g. type
A to add). The selected screen option will be highlighted.

 Please note: Mouse users may select an option by clicking the mouse.

The `Current' message is highlighted on the screen.


 (P)rev:     Make the previous message the current message.

 (N)ext:     Make the next message the current message.

 (A)dd:      Add the messages to the file. Information will always be
             inserted  into the file in date (and time) order. To add a
             message, firstly enter the date and the message itself. If
             appropriate, DAY-BY-DAY will prompt you for further information
             (i.e. duration, range, time).

 (D)elete:   The current message (highlighted).

 (U)pdate:   Used to edit date/time/contents of the current message. DAY-BY-
             DAY will prompt you for the new information, with the existing
             information offered as a default. This option is particularly
             useful for updating a birthday/annual meeting, etc.

 (B)ackward: Used to move the previous page of information.

 (F)orward:  Used to move the next page of information. If another page does
             not exist, DAY-BY-DAY will return to the main menu.

 (O)utput:   Used to print the current screen. DAY-BY-DAY will then automat-
             ically move forward onto the next screen.

 (E)xit:     Used to exit from the current screen and return to the main
             menu.



 MENU MODE  -  THE MAIN MENU
-----------------------------
 Having loaded DAY-BY-DAY, and used FORWARD to scroll through the different
screens (or EXIT), you will be presented with the main menu.

 To select options from the main menu simply press the key corresponding to
the option (e.g. F for Forthcoming engagements, M for Month planner).

 Please note: Mouse users may select an option by clicking the mouse.

 As mentioned previously, it is possible to go back and view the URGENT/
OVERDUE/THIS WEEK messages by selecting the appropriate option from the main
menu (i.e. 1 for Urgent, -for Overdue, =for This Week). ?Thats what it says!



 FORTHCOMING ENGAGEMENTS
-------------------------
 Use this option to display all messages from today's date onwards. Messages
will be displayed on a month by month basis (using FORWARD option). When you
have reached the end of the file (i.e. there are no more messages) DAY-BY-
DAY will display:

                    *** NO MORE ENTRIES ***


 OVERDUE
---------
 Use this option to display all messages that are overdue (i.e. prior to
todays date).



 THIS WEEK
-----------
 Use this option to display all messages that are dated today or the next
six days.



 CATEGORIES
------------
 Used tp group related messages. You may set up a maximum of 9 categories.

 For example, in the category called `Urgent', you would enter any urgent
messages by selecting the categories from the main menu. This will take you
into SCREEN mode - (within the urgent category) at which point you can enter
the message. The category heading (as per the main menu) will be displayed
at the top of the screen.
 As a result, this option provides the means to search and display messages
in particular grouping (in this case Urgent).
 URGENT is apre-defined category. New categories may be set up using CHANGE
CATEGORIES (see next section).
 Messages entered into a category will not only be displayed under the
selected category, but also under Forthcoming Engagements/Overdue/This Week.
 Information may be added without a date in a category. This is achieved by
accepting the default date of 0 when adding the message. Such an entry will
ONLY be displayed under the category heading. Hence, a category `NOTEPAD'
may be created which would be suitable for reminders which are not dependent
on the date.



 CHANGE CATEGORIES
-------------------
 Select option C from the main menu. A sub-menu will appear (at the bottom
of the screen). Simply type the first letter corresponding to the screen
option (e.g. type A to add). The selected screen option will be delighted.

 Please Note: Mouse users may select an option by clicking the mouse.

 (A)dd:       Adds a new category. The heading of this category will then
              automatically be added to the main menu. You may enter up to 9
              categories and to 12 characters per category heading.

 (D)elete:    You will be prompted for the category number (as displayed on
              the main menu). Any messages still remaining under a deleted
              category will only be displayed under forthcoming Engagements,
              Overdue and This Week as appropriate. Any undated messages
              will be displayed under Overdue.
               It is not possible to delete the `URGENT' category.

 (R)ename:    Rename any category. Firstly enter the category number (as
              displayed on the main menu) and the new category name. Every
              category may be renamed, including Urgent.



 JUMP TO A DATE
----------------
 Option J from the main menu. Firstly, enter the date and then all the
messages from the date will be displayed, month by month (you will be in
Forthcoming Engagements).



 MONTH PLANNER
---------------
 Option M from the main menu. The current month will be displayed.

 MMMM above the day represents any morning engagements.

 AAAA below the day represents any afternoon engagements.

 (P)rev:    Used to move to the previous month.

 (N)ext:    Used to move to the next month.

 (O)utput:  Used to print the current screen. DAY-BY-DAY will then
            automatically move forward onto the next screen.

 (E)xit:    Used to exit from the current screen and return to the main
            menu.



 WEEK PLANNER
--------------
 Option W from the main menu. The current week will now be displayed. XX
represents the time of any engagements (24 hr clock).

 (P)rev:    Used to move to the previous week.

 (N)ext:    Used to move to the next week.

 (O)utput:  Used to print the current screen. DAY-BY-DAY will then
            automatically move forward onto the next screen.

 (E)xit:    Used to exit from the current screen and return to the main
            menu.



 SEARCH
--------
 Option S from the main menu. Use this option to search for message, or part
of a message. You will be prompted to enter the requirement of your search
(if you just press RETURN, all the messages will be displayed). The search
is case independent (i.e. it does not discriminate between upper and lower
case letters).



 OPTIONS
---------
 Options are used to determine the amount of information to be prompted for
each message. The Options are Duration, Range and Time. When you load DAY-BY
-DAY, all of these options will be set to OFF, thus when entering messages
the minimum amount of information is required. To switch them ON simply
select the letter corresponding to the option. Select the letter again to
switch the OFF.

 Please Note: Mouse users can select an option by clicking the mouse.

 DURATION:  Setting this option to ON results in DAY-BY-DAY requesting (when
            adding an entry): Does this fill: The options are,
            (N)one, (M)orning,(A)fternoon,(W)hole.

            Use this to identify morning and afternoon appointments on the
            Month Planner.

 RANGE:     Setting this option to ON results in DAY-BY-DAY requesting (when
            adding an entry): How many entries: (You may enter up to 99).
            Days between entries: (e.g. 1 for daily,7 for weekly,etc.)

            Use this option if you wish to enter an appointment/message over
            a `range" of dates (e.g. town hall meeting every fortnight).

 TIME:      Setting this option to ON results in DAY-BY-DAY requesting the
            of the message (when adding an entry). Enter the starting time
            in hours and minutes. Simply press RETURN for minutes and a
            default 0 will be entered. After the starting time, enter the
            finishing time in the same way.

            Use this option to plan your day to the minute and this will be
            displayed on your Week Planner.

 Using any of the above options will be reflected in the screen display and
Weekly/Monthly Planners.



